Description: Upper left corner of papyrus cartonnage hypocephalus, yellow painted plaster uppermost with black designs including hieroglyphic text (name of deceased not visible), two registers of deities including, on upper register, Ihet cow and four sons of Horus, and on lower register sun-barque with Horus spearing Aapep, and child at prow of facing second bark of sun-god, below inverted register with remains of vignette with baboons in adoration.
